[I would be grateful for further distribution of the job advertisement=20
below]

In the newly founded Theoretical Computer Science group (Chair 8) at the=20
University of Erlangen-N=FCrnberg, several research positions are=20
available that can be filled at the doctoral or post-doctoral level.=20
These include project positions of up to two years, in the TV-L E13 or=20
E14 pay scale depending on qualification of the applicant; project=20
topics include

 	- coalgebraic logic
 	- probabilistic description logic
 	- formal methods in mechanical engineering.

Additionally, at least one position is available that is not tied to a=20
specific research project but does carry a teaching obligation of 5h per=20
week; in this case, research work can be positioned in any of the core=20
fields of the group including

 	- modal logic
 	- knowledge representation
 	- coalgebra
 	- formal methods
 	- program semantics
 	- applications of semantic technologies

Such positions can be filled at TV-L E13 for an initial appointment of=20
three years, with a possibility of extension for another three years=20
subject to provisions by German laws on temporal employment in academia;=20
postdoctoral applicants from EU countries can be appointed at the A13=20
payscale ("akademischer Rat") (which pays better and has better=20
benefits) for two periods of three years, with a possible extension of=20
two periods of two years at the A14 payscale ("akademischer Oberrat")=20
for candidates who successfully complete a habilitation during the first=20
six years.

Please send applications consisting of a cover letter, resume, and=20
contact details of three references by email to=20
lutz.schroeder@cs.fau.de. There is no particular application deadline;=20
positions will be filled when suitable candidates are found.

Best regards,

Lutz




